//Write a C program to find the factorial of the given input:

#include<stdio.h>
int main()
{
	int n,fact=1,i;
	printf("Enter the value of n = ");
	scanf("%d",&n);
	if(int(n) && n>=0)
	{
		for(i=1;i<=n;i++)
		{
			fact=fact*i;
		}
	printf("The factorial of the number %d = %d",n,fact);
	}
	else 
	{
		printf("Invalid input");
	}
	return 0;
}




Test cases:

Case 1:

Enter the value of n = 0
Invalid input

Case 2:

Enter the value of n = -5
Invalid input

Case 3:

Enter the value of n = 1
The factorial of the number 1 = 1




Case 4:

Enter the value of n = o
Invalid input

Case 5:

Enter the value of n = 13
The factorial of the number 13 = 1932053504
